# Web Artifacts Builder

Build powerful, self-contained frontend artifacts that bundle into a single HTML file.

**Stack**: React 18 + TypeScript + Vite + Parcel (bundling) + Tailwind CSS 3.4.1 + shadcn/ui

## Design Principles

**CRITICAL**: Avoid "AI slop" aesthetics — no excessive centered layouts, purple gradients, uniform rounded corners, or Inter font. Every artifact should feel intentionally designed.

## Workflow

### Step 1: Initialize Project

```bash
# Create a new React project with full toolchain
npx create-vite <project-name> --template react-ts
cd <project-name>
npm install
```

Configure the project with:
- ✅ React + TypeScript (via Vite)
- ✅ Tailwind CSS 3.4.1 with shadcn/ui theming system
- ✅ Path aliases (`@/`) configured in tsconfig and vite.config
- ✅ shadcn/ui components installed (`npx shadcn@latest init` then add needed components)
- ✅ All Radix UI dependencies included
- ✅ Parcel configured for bundling

### Step 2: Develop the Artifact

Build the application using React components, shadcn/ui primitives, and Tailwind CSS. Structure:

```
src/
├── components/
│   ├── ui/          # shadcn/ui primitives
│   └── features/    # Feature-specific components
├── lib/
│   └── utils.ts     # Utility functions (cn helper, etc.)
├── App.tsx          # Main application component
└── main.tsx         # Entry point
```

### Step 3: Bundle to Single HTML

To create a self-contained artifact with all JS, CSS, and dependencies inlined:

```bash
# Install bundling dependencies
npm install --save-dev parcel @parcel/config-default parcel-resolver-tspaths html-inline

# Create .parcelrc for path alias support
cat > .parcelrc << 'EOF'
{
  "extends": "@parcel/config-default",
  "resolvers": ["parcel-resolver-tspaths", "..."]
}
EOF

# Build and inline
npx parcel build index.html --no-source-maps
npx html-inline -i dist/index.html -o bundle.html -b dist
```

This creates `bundle.html` — a self-contained artifact with everything inlined.

### Step 4: Share the Artifact

Present the bundled HTML file to the user or deploy it.

### Step 5: Test (Optional)

Use Playwright, Puppeteer, or browser dev tools to verify functionality. Avoid upfront testing unless specifically requested — present first, iterate later.

## Component Reference

**shadcn/ui components**: https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components

Pre-install commonly needed components:
```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button card dialog dropdown-menu input label select separator sheet sidebar skeleton table tabs textarea toast tooltip
```

## Key Patterns

### State Management
- Use React hooks (`useState`, `useReducer`) for component state
- Use Zustand for global state if needed
- Use TanStack Query for server state

### Routing (if needed)
- Use React Router for multi-page artifacts
- Keep routing simple — hash-based routing works well for single-file bundles

### Responsive Design
- Mobile-first with Tailwind breakpoints
- Test at common breakpoints: 375px, 768px, 1024px, 1440px
